## Changes (Fresh-context remediation)

### 1. Schema and migration security
- Added buyer fields to `User` and `Order`; per-item tax/discount to `OrderItem`.
- Renamed `InvoiceSequence.currentNumber` → `lastNumber`.
- Replaced `Invoice.xmlContent/xmlUrl/pdfUrl` and `CreditNote.xmlContent/xmlUrl/pdfUrl` with `signedXml`, `xmlKey`, `pdfKey`.
- Migration: `apps/api/prisma/migrations/20260628000000_sri_security_remediation/migration.sql` (idempotent).

### 2. Storage layer returns R2 keys only
- `StorageService.uploadBuffer` returns `{ key }`.
- `SriDocumentStorageService` persists keys and generates signed URLs on demand.
- DTOs and shared types no longer expose `xmlContent` or `pdfUrl`.

### 3. Order creation buyer/tax population
- `OrdersService.createOrder` populates `customerName`, `customerIdentification`, `customerAddress` from Clerk profile/DTO.
- Per-item `taxRate`, `taxAmount`, `discountAmount` allocated on `OrderItem`.
- `ClerkWebhookService` syncs `name` and `public_metadata.identification` into `User`.

### 4. Payment webhook raw-body verification
- `PaymentWebhookController` and `PaymentWebhookService` use raw request body for signature verification.

### 5. SRI queue idempotency and resilience
- `SriQueueService` retries existing failed jobs instead of duplicating.
- `InvoicesService.retryIssue`/`retryCreditNote` guard against non-allowed statuses.
- `SriQueueWorker` reuses sequence/accessKey on retry and skips authorized overwrites.
- `SriQueueModule` gates queue/worker behind `SRI_QUEUE_ENABLED` and fails fast when Redis is unreachable.
- `sri-queue.config.ts` helpers expose queue env vars for E2E overrides.

### 6. SOAP/XML builder robustness
- `SriSoapClient` WSDL and per-call timeouts.
- XML builders fall back to consumidor-final only when buyer data is missing; use per-item `taxAmount`.

### 7. Dependency and tooling pins
- Pinned `node-forge@1.4.0` and `fast-xml-parser@5.9.3`.
- Added SRI queue/delivery env vars to `turbo.json`.

### 8. Test updates
- Updated unit/E2E tests for schema, DTO, signature, and queue behavior.
- Disabled SRI queue in E2E `TEST_CONFIG` by default to avoid Redis teardown errors.

### 9. Task 6.7 — end-to-end SRI flow E2E
- Added `apps/api/test/sri-invoice-flow.e2e-spec.ts` covering:
  - Stripe webhook → `SriQueueService.addIssueInvoiceJob` + PENDING job metadata
  - Admin `POST /v1/invoices/:id/retry` for FAILED invoices
  - Admin `GET /v1/invoices/:id/xml|pdf` redirects to signed URLs (no public R2 exposure)

## Changes (Focused re-review — 3 remaining BLOCKERS fixed)

### 10. R3-CRITICAL-2 — Consumidor final identification must be 13 digits
- Changed default `identificacionComprador` from `'9999999999'` (10 digits) to `'9999999999999'` (13 digits) in:
  - `apps/api/src/invoices/sri/sri-xml.builder.ts`
  - `apps/api/src/invoices/sri/sri-credit-note-xml.builder.ts`
- Added `isValidCedula` and `isValidEcuadorCustomerIdentification` helpers to `@repo/shared-utils`.
- Added custom `IsEcuadorCustomerIdentification` class-validator decorator at `apps/api/src/common/validators/is-ecuador-customer-identification.validator.ts`.
- Applied decorator to `CreateOrderDto.customerIdentification` so only valid Ecuadorian IDs are accepted (10-digit cédula, 13-digit RUC, or 13-digit consumidor final).

### 11. R3-CRITICAL-3 — `totalSinImpuestos` mismatch in invoice XML
- Updated `SriXmlBuilder` so document-level `totalSinImpuestos` is `subtotal - discountAmount` (post-discount), matching the sum of detail lines.
- `totalDescuento` remains `discountAmount` and `totalConImpuestos.baseImponible` already matched.
- Added unit-test assertions for matching totals after discount in `sri-xml.builder.spec.ts`.

### 12. R4-CRITICAL-4 — Persist invoice/credit-note record before SRI call
- Added `PENDING` to `InvoiceStatus` and `CreditNoteStatus` enums so pre-submission records can express "allocated, awaiting SRI submission".
- Migration: `apps/api/prisma/migrations/20260629000000_add_pending_document_status/migration.sql`.
- Refactored `SriQueueWorker.issueDocument` to call new `persistPreSubmissionDocument` immediately after allocating sequence/accessKey and before SRI submission.
  - Invoice: `upsert` by `orderId` with `status: PENDING`, `sriStatus: PENDING`, `sequenceNumber`, `accessKey`.
  - Credit note: `update` by `id` with the same pending fields.
- On retry, existing records already carry `sequenceNumber`/`accessKey`, so `issueDocument` reuses them instead of allocating new ones.
- `persistDocumentResult` now updates the same record rather than creating a new one.
- Updated `InvoicesService.retryIssue`/`retryCreditNote` to allow retries from `PENDING` status.
- Added/updated worker tests asserting pre-persist `PENDING` and sequence reuse on retry.

